#: ../../A/anti-idiotarianism.rst:5
msgid "anti-idiotarianism"
msgstr "anti-idiotarianism"

#: ../../A/anti-idiotarianism.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../A/anti-idiotarianism.rst:9
msgid ""
"[very common] Opposition to idiots of all political stripes. First coined in"
" the :ref:`blog` named `Little Green Footballs "
"<http://www.littlegreenfootballs.com/weblog/weblog.php>`_\\  as part of a "
"post expressing disgust with inane responses to post-9/11 Islamic terrorism."
" Anti-idiotarian wrath has focused on Islamic terrorists and their "
"sympathizers in the Western political left, but also routinely excoriated "
"right-wing politicians backing repressive ’anti-terror‘ legislation and "
"Christian religious figures who (in the blogosphere's view of the matter) "
"have descended nearly to the level of jihad themselves."
msgstr ""
"[非常に一般的]あらゆる政治的立場のばか者(idiot)に対する反対。`Little Green Footballs "
"<http://www.littlegreenfootballs.com/weblog/weblog.php>`_ という名の\\ "
":ref:`blog`\\ で、9.11後のイスラム過激派テロへのばかげた反応への嫌悪を表す投稿の一部として最初に造語された。anti-"
"idiotarianの怒りは、イスラム過激派のテロリストと、西側政治の左派にいる彼らの同調者に向けられてきたが、抑圧的な‘反テロ’立法を後押しする右派の政治家や、(ブログ界の見方では)ほとんどジハードそのものの水準にまで堕したキリスト教の宗教的人物をも、日常的に痛烈に非難してきた。"
